The paper deals with a problem in autonomous exploration and inspection with mobile robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using imitation learning, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing and adapting to different object distributions, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or control systems (cs.SY).
